Decision Tree Classification
Project Overview

This project uses a Decision Tree Classifier to classify different types of wine based on their chemical properties. Decision Trees are interpretable machine learning models commonly used for classification and decision-making tasks.

Dataset

Dataset Name: Wine Dataset

Source: Scikit-Learn Built-in Dataset

Dataset Description

The dataset contains the results of chemical analysis of wines grown in the same region in Italy.

Total Samples: 178
Features: 13
Classes: 3 Wine Categories
Feature Examples
Alcohol
Malic Acid
Ash
Magnesium
Flavanoids
Technologies Used
Python
Scikit-Learn
NumPy
Algorithm

Decision Tree Classifier

Evaluation Metrics
Accuracy Score
Classification Report
Confusion Matrix
Expected Outcome

The model predicts wine categories based on chemical composition and demonstrates the decision-making process of Decision Trees.
